'''PJKT Fest''' (also known as '''Projekt Fest''' or '''Projekt Community Festival''') is a recurring annual community convention in [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat|VRChat]] organized by [[Community:PJKT|Projekt: Community]] (PJKT). It is the organization's flagship summer event and has been held each year since 2023. The festival brings VRChat communities into a dedicated festival world for multi-day runs built around staffed booths and a published daily program.

==Overview==

PJKT Fest is typically scheduled in June or early July. Editions have ranged from a three-day inaugural weekend to roughly ten- and eleven-day runs in later years.<ref name="fa-2023-promo">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/52815205/ "PJKTCOM 2023 - Projekt Community Festival Promo 1"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity'' (posted June 2023). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref><ref name="fa-2024-poster">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/57219284/ "PJKT: Festival 2024 - Promo Poster"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity'' (posted 2024; includes event dates, participating community list, and world link). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref><ref name="ffvdgames-2025">[https://www.ffvdgames.com/2025/06/26/im-going-to-be-at-pjktfest-2025/ "I'm Going To Be At PJKT:FEST 2025!"] on ''Flippin' Fun Video Games'' (June 26, 2025). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> Booth and program applications are published ahead of each edition under Projekt / PJKT festival branding.<ref name="fa-2024-signups">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/56443199/ "Projekt: Community Festival 2024 - Sign-Ups Open!"] on ''Fur Affinity'' (community-uploaded event publicity; includes historical dates and links). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

==Format==

Fest is organized as a convention floor rather than a single-track show. VRChat groups and individual organizers staff booths to recruit members, demo projects, and host sessions, while a daily schedule rotates panels, workshops, entertainment, and meetups.<ref name="fa-2024-poster"/><ref name="ffvdgames-2025"/> Past program has covered topics such as sign language, improv, and virtual fitness, alongside live music and showcases of VRChat creative work.<ref name="ffvdgames-2025"/>

Participating communities have included gamers, roleplayers, improv groups, social clubs, avatar PvP combat groups, and larger networks such as the Furry Events Community, Soaring Fitness, TailBass, and the ProtoFox Network.<ref name="fa-2024-poster"/> The program is typically livestreamed on Projekt Community's Twitch channel, with recordings posted to its YouTube channel afterward.<ref name="ffvdgames-2025"/>

==History==

===2023===

The inaugural Projekt Community Festival ran from June 23 to 25, 2023.<ref name="fa-2023-promo"/> The three-day event brought together content creators, roleplaying groups, marketing organizations, and social groups, who set up booths to promote their organizations and recruit members.<ref name="fa-2023-promo"/>

===2024===

PJKT Fest 2024 ran from June 28 to July 8, 2024, spanning eleven days.<ref name="fa-2024-poster"/> In addition to the usual community booth floor, the edition featured a collaboration with [[wikipedia:Virtual Market (event)|Virtual Market]] (VKET).<ref name="fa-2024-vket">[https://furaffinity.net/view/57373666/ "PJKT: Fest 2024 - VKET Meet"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

===2025===

PJKT Fest 2025 was a ten-day event.<ref name="ffvdgames-2025"/> It continued the staffed-booth format with a daily changing program, and sessions were streamed and archived through Projekt Community's Twitch and YouTube channels.<ref name="ffvdgames-2025"/>

===2026===

On March 18, 2026, VRChat's Bluesky account announced that the 2026 edition was going ahead and that communities could sign up to take part.<ref name="vrchat-bsky">[https://bsky.app/profile/vrchat.com VRChat (@vrchat.com)] on ''Bluesky'' (post dated March 18, 2026 regarding PJKT Fest 2026 sign-ups). Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

==Participation==

Registration for booths and program is handled through Projekt Community's website and linked social channels. Requirements, deadlines, and participation rules are published with each year's call for applications.<ref name="fa-2024-signups"/> In previous years, applications were accepted for booth representatives, event hosts, and film festival submissions tied to PJKT's wider calendar.<ref name="fa-2024-signups"/>

